Score Keeper üèè

A lightweight, mobile-responsive web application for scoring cricket matches in real-time. Built entirely with vanilla web technologies, this app is perfect for tracking local matches, tournaments, or casual games with friends.

Live Demo: 
[scorekeeper.online](https://scorekeeper.online)

‚ú® Features

* **Interactive Match Setup:** Set custom over limits before the match begins.
* **Real-Time Tracking:** Tracks runs, wickets, overs, and dynamically calculates the target and required run rate for the second innings.
* **Comprehensive Keypad:** One-click buttons for legal runs (0-6), Wides (WD), No Balls (NB), and Wickets (OUT).
* **Advanced Extras Logic:** * Custom modals to handle complex deliveries like No Balls with runs off the bat, or No Balls resulting in a run-out.
    * A custom `+` button to add penalty or overthrow runs to the previous delivery.
* **Undo Functionality:** Made a mistake? The "Undo" button rolls back the exact state of the previous ball.
* **Live Scorecard:** A built-in modal that displays a ball-by-ball breakdown of both the 1st and 2nd innings.
* **Engaging UI/UX:** Features a dark-mode interface, an animated bat-and-ball intro screen, and a confetti celebration screen for the winning team.

 üõ†Ô∏è Tech Stack

* **HTML5:** Semantic structure and layout.
* **CSS3:** Custom variables, flexbox/grid layouts, and keyframe animations for the UI.
* **Vanilla JavaScript:** Core game logic, state management, and DOM manipulation without any external libraries.

